The article states that the Polish government's investigation into the explosion near the border with Ukraine is being commended for its professionalism and thoroughness. The US government is not jumping to conclusions and is gathering information while remaining in contact with Polish officials. The preliminary assessment suggests that the explosion was caused by a Ukrainian air defense missile that accidentally landed in Poland. The US government will continue to assess and share any new information transparently. Regardless of the final conclusions, it is believed that Russia is ultimately responsible for the incident, as they launched missiles targeting civilian infrastructure in Ukraine. The US expresses solidarity with Ukraine and offers condolences for the losses suffered in the airstrikes. The article also mentions that millions of Ukrainians are without basic necessities as a result of the attacks. Thoughts and prayers are extended to the loved ones of the two Polish citizens who were tragically killed.